- Root cause: Angular component CSS is scoped with attribute selectors and
  cannot override global .pc-sidebar rules. Moving .pc-sidebar.lis-sidebar
  overrides to styles.css fixes light/dark/hover/active in both themes.
- Light theme: deep forest green #04342C background (was rendering as white bg-surface)
- Dark theme: #031f19 (now explicitly re-asserted so data-theme=dark slate doesn't win)
- Active state: teal-tinted bg + #9FE1CB text + teal icon
- Hover state: subtle white overlay rgba(255,255,255,0.07)
- Section captions: uppercase 9.5px, 28% white opacity
- Nav items: 8px radius, proper padding, smooth 130ms transitions
- Footer: dark overlay bg, correct user name/role colors
- Sidebar component CSS now only has scoped atoms: brand icon, avatar, badge, mobile-close
---
